text:
🇷🇺 💬  Déclarations du ministre russe des Affaires étrangères, Sergueï Lavrov, lors d’une réunion des ministres des Affaires étrangères des pays du G20:

🔹Certains délégations occidentales ont transformé les travaux liés à l’agenda du G20 en vaudeville, ayant pour but de rejeter à la Russie la responsabilité de leurs propres échecs économiques;

🔹La Russie insiste sur une enquête rapide et juste avec sa participation sur le sabotage des gazoducs Nord Stream 1 et 2;

🔹La Russie plaide pour que les pays émergents puissent jouer un rôle plus important au sein du FMI, de la Banque mondiale et de l'OMC;

🔹L'Occident crée des obstacles aux exportations de produits agricoles russes, même si les représentants de l'UE disent le contraire;

🔹"Faire bloc" aux sanctions illégitimes et aux violations de la liberté du commerce international est une nécessité;

🔹L'Occident "enterre sans scrupule" l'initiative du Secrétaire général de l'ONU de transférer gratuitement les engrais russes à l'Afrique;

🔹La Russie est déterminée à créer des systèmes de paiement indépendants et à étendre les règlements en monnaie nationale au sein des BRICS, de l'OCS et de l'UEEA.
____
RRussian Foreign Ministry - МИД России

Google_Trans:
🇷🇺 💬 Statements by Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov at a G20 Foreign Ministers' Meeting:

🔹Some Western delegations have turned the G20 agenda into a farce, aiming to shift the blame for their own economic failures onto Russia;

🔹Russia insists on a swift and fair investigation, with its participation, into the sabotage of the Nord Stream 1 and 2 gas pipelines;

🔹Russia advocates for emerging economies to play a greater role in the IMF, the World Bank, and the WTO;

🔹The West is creating obstacles to Russian agricultural exports, even though EU representatives claim otherwise;

🔹Standing united against illegitimate sanctions and violations of free international trade is essential;

🔹The West "unscrupulously buries" the UN Secretary-General's initiative to transfer Russian fertilizers to Africa free of charge;

🔹Russia is determined to create independent payment systems and expand settlements in national currencies within the BRICS, SCO, and EAEU.

____ Russian Foreign Ministry - МИД России

text:
Notice on Collecting Fingerprints for Visa Application

According to the relevant regulations of China, starting from 19 January 2023, fingerprints of both hands of an visa applicant will be collected at the Chinese Embassy in The Bahamas.

1. Please be noted that all applicants are requested to go to the Embassy in person for biometric data collection. Visitors to China are responsible for all the consequences in case of entry rejection due to forged or substituted fingerprints.

2. Exemption is granted to the following categories of applicants:
I. Applicants under the age of 14 or over the age of 70;
II. Diplomatic passport holders, or applicants who are eligible for diplomatic, official and courtesy visas;
III. Applicants holding the same passport with fingerprints collected within 5 years. (The exemption will only be granted when the biometric sticker visa is still identifiable. Otherwise, the exemption will only be granted at the embassy or consular office where the fingerprints were originally collected.);
IV. Applicants with all ten fingers mutilated or all ten fingerprints uncollectible.

3. An applicant must complete and print the visa application form through China Online Visa Application system (https://cova.mfa.gov.cn), and make appointment thereby well ahead of departure. The applicant shall go in person to the Embassy on the appointed date to submit the printed form and the visa application materials and has his or her finger prints collected.

